    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 4 c-e shows reduced head width and increased neck length of dendritic spines upon shRNA-mediated Srgap2 knock down.\nFigure 4 f-h shows increased head width and decreased neck length of dendritic spines upon overexpression of Srgap2\nFigure 5 shows a dose dependent effect of Srgap2 depletion in heterozygous and knock out neurons: in juvenile mice (P18-21) dendritic spine head width is reduced, neck length is increased and spine density is increased (Fig.5 C,-F). In adult mice (P65-77) dendritic spine neck length is increased and spine density is increased.. Experimental description: The Srgap2 knock-out strain was a gene trapped (GT) allele of Srgap2 (B6;129P2-Srgap2Gt(XH102)Byg/Mmcd) obtained from Mutant Mouse Regional Resource Centers (MMRRC). Mice homozygous for this allele were referred to as Srgap2 KO (knock-out).",
